1
00:02:06,280 --> 00:02:08,000
<i>I don't have much time left.</i>

2
00:02:08,080 --> 00:02:10,680
<i>I'd rather spend it</i>
<i>collecting as much happiness as I can.</i>

3
00:02:10,759 --> 00:02:13,720
I have to check on a hotel project
in Mae Hong Son.

4
00:02:14,240 --> 00:02:15,320
Want to come with me?

5
00:02:15,400 --> 00:02:17,560
<i>Maybe we met by coincidence.</i>

6
00:02:17,640 --> 00:02:21,480
But we'll stay together long enough
for it to become destiny.

7
00:02:21,560 --> 00:02:22,760
<i>With comets,</i>

8
00:02:22,840 --> 00:02:27,480
<i>astronomers can calculate</i>
<i>when they'll return.</i>

9
00:02:28,800 --> 00:02:29,880
<i>But with people,</i>

10
00:02:30,840 --> 00:02:33,440
we never know when we'll meet again.

11
00:02:33,520 --> 00:02:36,200
That's why they say, if you keep waiting,

12
00:02:36,280 --> 00:02:37,960
you might miss your chance forever.

13
00:02:46,240 --> 00:02:47,360
Can I ask you something?

14
00:02:47,440 --> 00:02:50,520
Has Pun come back from the South yet?

15
00:02:53,400 --> 00:02:55,840
Pun, today is Mungmink's birthday.

16
00:02:55,920 --> 00:02:57,560
Take this gift to her for me.

17
00:02:58,080 --> 00:03:00,440
Could it be another day, Mom?
I want to clear my work.

18
00:03:00,520 --> 00:03:03,080
Come on. You already went to work there.

19
00:03:03,160 --> 00:03:05,120
When you're back,
you should rest sometimes.

20
00:03:05,200 --> 00:03:07,360
Go see her. Consider it a break.

21
00:03:07,440 --> 00:03:08,720
Please, honey.

22
00:03:12,120 --> 00:03:13,440
Mom, can't it be another day?

23
00:03:13,520 --> 00:03:16,120
Uncle Dech has helped me
with so many things.

24
00:03:16,640 --> 00:03:20,240
He even carried beautiful fabrics
across the sea for me.

25
00:03:20,320 --> 00:03:22,280
I don't want to refuse.

26
00:03:22,880 --> 00:03:25,160
Help me out, Pun. Please?

27
00:03:25,240 --> 00:03:26,680
Later, Mom. I'll bring it to her.

28
00:03:26,760 --> 00:03:29,080
It has to be today. Go on.

29
00:03:29,160 --> 00:03:31,640
Mom, I really have to work today.
Otherwise, I won't finish.

30
00:03:31,720 --> 00:03:32,760
Pun.

31
00:03:32,840 --> 00:03:35,160
Seriously, Mom.
Let me finish my work first.

32
00:03:35,240 --> 00:03:37,080
- Then I'll go give it to her.
- Pun!

33
00:04:07,320 --> 00:04:08,640
Your birthday gift.

34
00:04:09,360 --> 00:04:10,600
My mom asked me to bring it.

35
00:04:13,680 --> 00:04:14,840
Thank you.

36
00:04:16,480 --> 00:04:18,680
- Where are your friends?
- No one came.

37
00:04:19,200 --> 00:04:20,279
Why?

38
00:04:20,360 --> 00:04:21,760
They said I'm too much.

39
00:04:22,360 --> 00:04:23,480
Are you, though?

40
00:04:27,360 --> 00:04:30,040
I just wanted a dress theme
so it would look nice.

41
00:04:30,120 --> 00:04:32,600
And I asked to pick the photos first,
so it would look good.

42
00:04:32,680 --> 00:04:33,920
That's good for everyone.

43
00:04:34,600 --> 00:04:36,480
Good for everyone or good for you alone?

44
00:04:40,720 --> 00:04:43,080
It's your event,
so doing things your way is fine.

45
00:04:43,160 --> 00:04:44,600
But your friends are guests.

46
00:04:45,160 --> 00:04:47,720
If they don't want to come,
that's their right.

47
00:04:47,800 --> 00:04:49,200
I know.

48
00:04:49,280 --> 00:04:51,600
But if they weren't happy,
why didn't they say it?

49
00:04:51,680 --> 00:04:54,920
If they didn't want the theme
or me picking photos, then say so.

50
00:04:55,000 --> 00:04:56,880
Why act like they'll come,
then not show up

51
00:04:56,960 --> 00:04:58,840
and talk behind my back? That's not fair.

52
00:04:58,920 --> 00:05:00,440
And were you fair to them?

53
00:05:01,200 --> 00:05:03,920
If a friend came off-theme,
or posted photos without telling you,

54
00:05:04,440 --> 00:05:05,840
would you go off on them?

55
00:05:09,760 --> 00:05:11,800
You can't blame only your friends.

56
00:05:11,880 --> 00:05:13,840
You have to look at yourself too.

57
00:05:15,520 --> 00:05:17,320
Ask yourself.

58
00:05:17,840 --> 00:05:20,240
Would you want to be friends
with someone that demanding?

59
00:05:21,120 --> 00:05:23,360
- Pun, you're scolding me.
- I'm not scolding you.

60
00:05:23,440 --> 00:05:25,920
I'm telling you the truth,
so you'll think about it.

61
00:05:28,600 --> 00:05:30,520
And I hope you do.

62
00:05:40,800 --> 00:05:42,000
Happy birthday.

63
00:05:43,720 --> 00:05:47,000
You're 22 now. Act like an adult.

64
00:05:59,680 --> 00:06:03,160
Hey, now I know what I want in this life.

65
00:06:03,240 --> 00:06:05,320
I want Pun.

66
00:06:05,400 --> 00:06:08,200
Huh? What are you going on about?

67
00:06:08,720 --> 00:06:09,720
I'm serious.

68
00:06:09,800 --> 00:06:13,720
My whole life, no one's ever scolded me
with good intentions before.

69
00:06:13,800 --> 00:06:15,080
Only Pun.

70
00:06:15,160 --> 00:06:17,520
I need someone like that in my life.

71
00:06:20,200 --> 00:06:22,720
What? How does that work, Mink?
I'm confused.

72
00:06:22,800 --> 00:06:25,520
Pun warned me not to be so extra.

73
00:06:25,600 --> 00:06:28,160
That's why my friends
didn't want to come to my party.

74
00:06:28,240 --> 00:06:31,720
I'm really impressed.

75
00:06:31,800 --> 00:06:33,800
All this time, guys who chased me

76
00:06:33,880 --> 00:06:35,320
said everything I did was perfect.

77
00:06:35,400 --> 00:06:37,160
They just went along with everything.

78
00:06:37,240 --> 00:06:39,320
But Pun is the first one

79
00:06:39,400 --> 00:06:41,000
who dared to tell me the truth.

80
00:06:41,080 --> 00:06:43,400
I want someone like Pun
as my life partner.

81
00:06:43,480 --> 00:06:45,480
And you have to help me, Rok.

82
00:06:45,560 --> 00:06:46,760
Please.

83
00:06:47,360 --> 00:06:48,640
That's not up to me.

84
00:06:48,720 --> 00:06:50,080
It's up to Pun.

85
00:06:50,160 --> 00:06:52,520
But you're the only one
who's closest to him.

86
00:06:52,600 --> 00:06:55,880
If you won't help me,
at least don't get in my way.

87
00:06:55,960 --> 00:06:57,920
And don't cheer for someone else
instead of me.

88
00:07:05,920 --> 00:07:07,200
This is ridiculous.

89
00:07:26,880 --> 00:07:29,040
Are you still overthinking about my mom?

90
00:07:29,120 --> 00:07:33,680
Smile. Like this.

91
00:07:54,480 --> 00:07:55,320
What?

92
00:07:57,800 --> 00:08:01,320
Let me work first. Okay?

93
00:08:06,200 --> 00:08:09,840
Win, let me work for just a second.

94
00:08:13,800 --> 00:08:15,840
You should do your homework instead.

95
00:08:15,920 --> 00:08:17,600
Hey, Win!

96
00:08:18,840 --> 00:08:20,400
Come on!

97
00:08:42,960 --> 00:08:44,520
I love you the most, Pie!

98
00:08:44,600 --> 00:08:47,280
I love you the most, Win!

99
00:09:03,120 --> 00:09:03,960
WOVEN FABRICS FROM HUAY TONG KOR

100
00:09:04,040 --> 00:09:05,600
Yes!

101
00:09:06,200 --> 00:09:07,360
Finished your work already?

102
00:09:08,440 --> 00:09:12,160
Yeah. Just the conclusion left,
then a final proofread for typos,

103
00:09:12,240 --> 00:09:13,520
and I'm done.

104
00:09:13,600 --> 00:09:15,440
Well done. Let me hug you.

105
00:09:17,400 --> 00:09:19,560
Come on. Hug me.

106
00:09:30,840 --> 00:09:31,880
Here.

107
00:09:34,000 --> 00:09:34,920
What is it?

108
00:09:37,280 --> 00:09:39,720
When you finish a project,
you deserve a gift.

109
00:09:48,320 --> 00:09:50,680
Win, that's so sweet.

110
00:09:51,960 --> 00:09:53,840
Why a bird?

111
00:09:54,680 --> 00:09:56,360
Because a bird can fly anywhere.

112
00:10:00,120 --> 00:10:01,520
Ever since we met,

113
00:10:01,600 --> 00:10:04,520
you've always said
you were born to obey your mom.

114
00:10:05,760 --> 00:10:07,760
You barely get to do anything you want.

115
00:10:09,240 --> 00:10:11,040
So I made this bird.

116
00:10:12,680 --> 00:10:15,640
It's my promise that one day,

117
00:10:16,240 --> 00:10:18,600
I'll help you live freely,

118
00:10:19,120 --> 00:10:21,320
the way you want to. Just like this bird.

119
00:10:38,360 --> 00:10:40,200
Thank you so much, Win.

120
00:10:41,840 --> 00:10:43,320
Really, thank you.

121
00:10:51,040 --> 00:10:51,920
Put it on for me.

122
00:11:09,760 --> 00:11:11,000
So cute.

123
00:11:13,840 --> 00:11:14,840
Do you like it?

124
00:11:15,560 --> 00:11:16,520
I do.

125
00:11:22,360 --> 00:11:23,560
Pie.

126
00:11:26,240 --> 00:11:28,840
Do you think your mom will accept us?

127
00:11:30,160 --> 00:11:32,360
You're a proper young lady.
I'm just an ordinary guy.

128
00:11:33,000 --> 00:11:34,560
I don't have anything.

129
00:11:36,720 --> 00:11:38,440
I'm not that different from you.

130
00:11:38,960 --> 00:11:40,960
These days, my family lives off old money.

131
00:11:41,680 --> 00:11:44,160
I'm not rich. Just used to be.

132
00:11:44,760 --> 00:11:45,920
Same here.

133
00:11:47,240 --> 00:11:50,240
It's like I have to start from zero again.

134
00:11:50,320 --> 00:11:51,640
At least I graduated.

135
00:11:51,720 --> 00:11:53,960
With the scholarship, I can study abroad.

136
00:11:55,160 --> 00:11:57,640
- The Japan scholarship you told me about?
- Yeah.

137
00:11:58,240 --> 00:11:59,960
The brother next door helped me find it.

138
00:12:00,040 --> 00:12:02,600
If there's a chance,
I'll introduce you to him later.

139
00:12:07,320 --> 00:12:08,800
About my mom, Win.

140
00:12:09,840 --> 00:12:12,120
She might have a really high wall.

141
00:12:13,400 --> 00:12:14,240
Well.

142
00:12:15,160 --> 00:12:17,560
She has a sore spot
about men taking advantage of women.

143
00:12:18,080 --> 00:12:20,560
My dad took her money to invest.

144
00:12:20,640 --> 00:12:22,640
In the end, he got someone new.

145
00:12:22,720 --> 00:12:24,840
When they split up,
he took a lot of her things.

146
00:12:25,360 --> 00:12:28,520
So she worries.
She doesn't want me taken advantage of.

147
00:12:29,280 --> 00:12:31,840
Pie, I'm not that kind of person.

148
00:12:31,920 --> 00:12:33,160
Don't worry.

149
00:12:36,760 --> 00:12:39,400
I believe love and sincerity

150
00:12:39,920 --> 00:12:42,000
will make your mom accept us.

151
00:12:44,200 --> 00:12:46,680
I'll win your mom over.

152
00:13:16,960 --> 00:13:19,160
- Wow.
- What are you buying so much for?

153
00:13:19,240 --> 00:13:20,400
- It's just the two of us.
- Snack!

154
00:13:20,480 --> 00:13:22,080
Your dad barely comes home.

155
00:13:22,160 --> 00:13:23,040
NEW

156
00:13:23,120 --> 00:13:25,480
I don't want to go out much, Mom,
so I'm stocking up.

157
00:13:26,600 --> 00:13:28,800
If you're buying this much,
why not come earlier?

158
00:13:28,880 --> 00:13:30,840
The supermarket's been open since ten.

159
00:13:30,920 --> 00:13:33,720
Why are you rushing here late at night,
like you're sneaking around.

160
00:13:33,800 --> 00:13:34,800
Afraid someone will see you?

161
00:13:34,880 --> 00:13:36,440
You know I've been busy.

162
00:13:36,520 --> 00:13:38,280
And I don't want to run into
friends either.

163
00:13:38,360 --> 00:13:39,200
Too tired to talk.

164
00:13:39,280 --> 00:13:41,040
They'll bring up work again.

165
00:13:41,120 --> 00:13:43,400
I'm stressed.
I can't ever finish anything.

166
00:13:44,120 --> 00:13:46,040
- Oh, Mom.
- What?

167
00:13:46,560 --> 00:13:47,960
- I forgot to gossip with you.
- What?

168
00:13:48,040 --> 00:13:50,360
Pun is eyeing Pie.

169
00:13:50,440 --> 00:13:51,600
And he wants me to help him set it up.

170
00:13:52,560 --> 00:13:54,200
Don't get involved.

171
00:13:54,280 --> 00:13:56,840
Nhun is a lot to deal with.
Don't start trouble for no reason.

172
00:13:56,920 --> 00:13:59,840
You can stop me, but you can't stop Pun.

173
00:14:00,520 --> 00:14:02,320
Yeah, true.

174
00:14:02,840 --> 00:14:05,280
Just like when your uncle
wanted to marry Nhun.

175
00:14:05,360 --> 00:14:07,360
Our family tried to stop it
again and again.

176
00:14:07,440 --> 00:14:10,640
We live simply. We're not rich like them.

177
00:14:10,720 --> 00:14:12,200
That side, wow.

178
00:14:12,280 --> 00:14:15,080
Rich, picky, all high-society.

179
00:14:15,160 --> 00:14:17,880
How could we stop it?
Your uncle never listened.

180
00:14:17,960 --> 00:14:20,040
He married her anyway. And what happened?

181
00:14:20,840 --> 00:14:22,760
He's still complaining. Serves him right.

182
00:14:23,520 --> 00:14:25,040
Your ears must be numb by now.

183
00:14:26,240 --> 00:14:28,160
If Pie and Pun really get married,

184
00:14:28,240 --> 00:14:30,160
you'll be the next one with numb ears.

185
00:14:31,080 --> 00:14:32,280
Mom!

186
00:14:33,240 --> 00:14:35,280
- This one's nice.
- Let's get snacks.

187
00:14:35,360 --> 00:14:37,080
This is good. I haven't had it in ages.

188
00:14:37,160 --> 00:14:38,480
- Mom.
- What now?

189
00:14:38,560 --> 00:14:40,600
Don't tell Uncle Sil
and Aunt Nhun about this.

190
00:14:40,680 --> 00:14:42,040
Let Pun tell them himself.

191
00:14:44,280 --> 00:14:47,680
Next time, if it's a secret,
don't tell me first.

192
00:14:47,760 --> 00:14:49,240
I don't want to deal with it.

193
00:14:49,320 --> 00:14:52,080
Go pay already. Hurry.

194
00:14:52,160 --> 00:14:53,120
I'll push the cart myself, Mom.

195
00:14:53,200 --> 00:14:55,040
- Fine. If you can push it, then go.
- Yeah, yeah.

196
00:14:55,120 --> 00:14:56,400
I never stay up late, okay?

197
00:14:57,040 --> 00:14:58,560
We've lived together this long.
Don't you know that?

198
00:14:58,640 --> 00:14:59,760
Where are you going now?

199
00:14:59,840 --> 00:15:01,520
- Hurry up!
- I'm going!

200
00:15:01,600 --> 00:15:03,920
- My face will sag, you hear me?
- I'm going! Mom…

201
00:15:04,000 --> 00:15:05,560
- Let's get home.
- Mom!

202
00:15:05,640 --> 00:15:07,960
- What? Watermelons again?
- Watermelons.

203
00:15:08,880 --> 00:15:11,320
What time am I going to get home?

204
00:15:11,400 --> 00:15:12,240
- I'm getting wrinkles
- Oh, shoot.

205
00:15:12,320 --> 00:15:14,880
- for sure.
- Four-zero-one-two.

206
00:15:14,960 --> 00:15:16,320
Hurry up. Hey!

207
00:15:16,400 --> 00:15:18,120
What's wrong, honey?

208
00:15:19,080 --> 00:15:20,800
- Mom, my stomach hurts.
- Stomach hurts?

209
00:15:20,880 --> 00:15:23,120
- It hurts.
- Which is it, bathroom or period cramps?

210
00:15:23,200 --> 00:15:25,320
- Maybe period cramps.
- Period cramps? Oh my God.

211
00:15:25,400 --> 00:15:26,600
What about your stuff?

212
00:15:26,680 --> 00:15:28,640
- Just leave it like that.
- That's a lot, honey.

213
00:15:28,720 --> 00:15:30,320
- Mom, let's go.
- She has a stomachache.

214
00:15:34,560 --> 00:15:36,800
- Rok. Feeling better now?
- Huh?

215
00:15:37,520 --> 00:15:38,440
Not yet.

216
00:15:38,520 --> 00:15:41,520
Let's go home. Stomach hurts.

217
00:15:51,720 --> 00:15:53,320
We were about to pay already.

218
00:15:53,400 --> 00:15:55,160
What's wrong with you?

219
00:15:56,440 --> 00:15:58,840
I told you, Mom. My stomach hurts.

220
00:15:58,920 --> 00:16:00,520
It really hurts.

221
00:16:00,600 --> 00:16:02,480
Let's go home. We can buy it online.

222
00:16:02,560 --> 00:16:04,480
- Hurry. Start the car.
- Okay.

223
00:16:07,880 --> 00:16:09,280
Why are you stopping, Puk?

224
00:16:09,360 --> 00:16:11,200
Ma'am, the wheel's stuck.

225
00:16:12,720 --> 00:16:14,760
I'll go get the car. Wait right here.

226
00:16:14,840 --> 00:16:16,240
Yes.

227
00:16:21,920 --> 00:16:23,320
Krarok?

228
00:16:27,760 --> 00:16:29,760
- Puk!
- Yes?

229
00:16:29,840 --> 00:16:31,640
I think I saw Krarok.

230
00:16:31,720 --> 00:16:33,440
Hang on.

231
00:16:33,520 --> 00:16:35,680
Isn't Miss Krarok
in Mae Hong Son with Miss Pie?

232
00:16:35,760 --> 00:16:37,160
That's what I thought.

233
00:16:37,240 --> 00:16:39,720
But I really did see her.
I even took pictures.

234
00:16:39,800 --> 00:16:42,000
Take a look. Does it look like Krarok?

235
00:16:42,080 --> 00:16:45,320
It's shaky and this blurry.
How could anyone tell?

236
00:16:45,400 --> 00:16:47,560
Maybe it's not Miss Krarok.

237
00:16:47,640 --> 00:16:49,640
But I'm sure it's her.

238
00:17:02,320 --> 00:17:03,520
That car from last night.

239
00:17:07,640 --> 00:17:08,560
Hey.

240
00:17:09,720 --> 00:17:11,040
I'm Krarok's friend's mother.

241
00:17:11,119 --> 00:17:13,280
I've brought her here a few times.

242
00:17:13,839 --> 00:17:15,400
- Is Krarok here?
- She's not.

243
00:17:15,480 --> 00:17:17,359
Miss Krarok left early this morning.

244
00:17:17,440 --> 00:17:20,240
This morning? Today?

245
00:17:20,319 --> 00:17:21,520
Yes.

246
00:17:21,599 --> 00:17:23,599
She'll probably be back this evening.

247
00:17:24,240 --> 00:17:27,880
Wait. When did Krarok get back
from Mae Hong Son?

248
00:17:27,960 --> 00:17:29,640
Miss Krarok didn't go anywhere.

249
00:17:29,720 --> 00:17:30,960
She's been in Bangkok the whole time.

250
00:17:31,040 --> 00:17:32,160
The whole time?

251
00:17:32,240 --> 00:17:34,280
You mean she never went up North?

252
00:17:34,360 --> 00:17:35,320
Yes.

253
00:17:35,400 --> 00:17:36,680
Swear you're telling the truth.

254
00:17:36,760 --> 00:17:38,720
Why would I lie to you?

255
00:17:38,800 --> 00:17:40,920
Don't tell anyone I came here.

256
00:17:41,000 --> 00:17:42,480
Yes.

257
00:17:44,840 --> 00:17:45,960
I can't take it.

258
00:17:46,560 --> 00:17:48,640
Here. Is this enough to keep you quiet?

259
00:17:48,720 --> 00:17:49,840
Keep your mouth shut.

260
00:17:49,920 --> 00:17:53,000
Don't tell anyone I was here. Got it?

261
00:17:54,200 --> 00:17:55,240
I understand.

262
00:18:03,840 --> 00:18:04,880
Pie.

263
00:18:22,080 --> 00:18:23,200
Pie.

264
00:18:25,760 --> 00:18:27,000
I'm going into town.

265
00:18:28,920 --> 00:18:29,960
Hey.

266
00:18:30,880 --> 00:18:32,600
The scholarship results
are out today, right?

267
00:18:34,000 --> 00:18:36,960
Yeah. I'm going to find somewhere
with a signal and check.

268
00:18:40,640 --> 00:18:45,560
I hope you get it, Win. I'm praying.

269
00:18:47,960 --> 00:18:48,920
Pie.

270
00:18:50,520 --> 00:18:52,200
If I get the scholarship to study,

271
00:18:53,480 --> 00:18:54,760
will you come with me?

272
00:18:55,360 --> 00:18:58,640
Oh, I don't know Japanese.

273
00:18:58,720 --> 00:18:59,560
Come on.

274
00:18:59,640 --> 00:19:02,280
You can learn it in no time. Come with me.

275
00:19:02,800 --> 00:19:06,000
Otherwise, we'll be apart,
and we won't see each other for ages.

276
00:19:06,640 --> 00:19:08,840
Don't think that far ahead yet.

277
00:19:08,920 --> 00:19:11,200
Go check the results first,
then we'll talk, okay?

278
00:19:12,080 --> 00:19:13,280
It's a sure thing.

279
00:19:13,360 --> 00:19:15,360
Get ready for a trip to Japan.

280
00:19:15,440 --> 00:19:16,720
Alright.

281
00:19:16,800 --> 00:19:18,040
Let's hug first.

282
00:19:25,560 --> 00:19:26,440
I'm going now.

283
00:19:30,640 --> 00:19:32,440
Good luck, Win.

284
00:20:28,440 --> 00:20:29,760
CONGRATULATIONS

285
00:20:29,840 --> 00:20:32,480
Yes! I got the scholarship!

286
00:20:41,120 --> 00:20:42,120
Huh?

287
00:20:42,200 --> 00:20:43,840
1% BATTERY

288
00:20:49,680 --> 00:20:50,920
Here.

289
00:21:04,320 --> 00:21:06,480
Win, you're back?

290
00:21:21,120 --> 00:21:22,120
Mom.

291
00:21:24,760 --> 00:21:26,200
Who is Win?

292
00:21:27,160 --> 00:21:29,040
He's the owner of this, right?

293
00:21:29,120 --> 00:21:30,560
Answer me, Pie.

294
00:21:30,640 --> 00:21:33,280
Answer your mother!

295
00:21:35,920 --> 00:21:38,400
Win…

296
00:21:38,960 --> 00:21:42,200
Win is the nephew of Aunt Saen,
who owns the homestay.

297
00:21:42,840 --> 00:21:45,360
The one you said takes you places,

298
00:21:45,440 --> 00:21:47,640
acts as your interpreter,
and looks after you?!

299
00:21:47,720 --> 00:21:49,920
The one you said was ten years old?!

300
00:21:53,200 --> 00:21:56,080
What kind of kid
wears underwear like this, Pie?!

301
00:22:03,960 --> 00:22:05,400
And his things

302
00:22:05,960 --> 00:22:07,960
are in your room like this.

303
00:22:08,680 --> 00:22:10,760
He's been sleeping here, hasn't he?

304
00:22:11,680 --> 00:22:12,520
Answer me!

305
00:22:12,600 --> 00:22:13,720
Mom.

306
00:22:13,800 --> 00:22:14,840
I'm sorry.

307
00:22:14,920 --> 00:22:16,440
I'm sorry, Mom.

308
00:22:16,520 --> 00:22:18,520
You're apologizing.

309
00:22:18,600 --> 00:22:20,560
That means

310
00:22:21,200 --> 00:22:23,080
you really did something wrong,
doesn't it?

311
00:22:27,520 --> 00:22:28,920
Pie!

312
00:22:30,880 --> 00:22:32,080
Mom…

313
00:22:33,160 --> 00:22:36,680
Do you know how heartbroken I am?

314
00:22:36,760 --> 00:22:40,680
You know you're the only thing
I have in this life.

315
00:22:41,840 --> 00:22:45,680
Why don't you ever think
about my feelings?

316
00:22:47,360 --> 00:22:51,400
You teamed up with your friend
and planned to deceive me.

317
00:22:51,480 --> 00:22:55,360
Just running away to stay here alone
was already breaking my heart!

318
00:22:55,960 --> 00:22:58,720
And now you bring a man to sleep here too?

319
00:22:59,240 --> 00:23:03,280
Huh? Do you want to shock me to death?

320
00:23:03,360 --> 00:23:05,040
Mom, I'm sorry.

321
00:23:05,120 --> 00:23:07,200
I'm really sorry.

322
00:23:07,280 --> 00:23:09,080
- I'm sorry.
- Go!

323
00:23:09,160 --> 00:23:10,760
Pack your things and go home.

324
00:23:10,840 --> 00:23:13,240
- Pack your things right now!
- No!

325
00:23:13,320 --> 00:23:14,800
Mom, I can't go yet.

326
00:23:14,880 --> 00:23:16,600
Why can't you go back?

327
00:23:16,680 --> 00:23:18,240
I haven't told Win yet!

328
00:23:18,320 --> 00:23:20,520
Oh my God, Pie!

329
00:23:20,600 --> 00:23:22,240
How did it turn out like this?

330
00:23:22,320 --> 00:23:25,440
- Mom!
- Why did you do this?

331
00:23:25,520 --> 00:23:26,880
Why? Why?!

332
00:23:26,960 --> 00:23:29,760
If you act like this,
a man won't value you.

333
00:23:29,840 --> 00:23:32,160
He'll think you're an easy woman.

334
00:23:32,240 --> 00:23:33,200
- Mom!
- Are you?!

335
00:23:33,280 --> 00:23:35,840
You're not packing, are you?

336
00:23:35,920 --> 00:23:38,560
Fine. Then don't pack.
Leave everything here.

337
00:23:38,640 --> 00:23:40,000
- Mom!
- Come home with me!

338
00:23:40,080 --> 00:23:43,080
- No, Mom. Let go!
- Come here right now!

339
00:23:43,160 --> 00:23:44,080
- Right now!
- Mom!

340
00:23:44,160 --> 00:23:46,000
- I'm not listening to anything!
- Pie!

341
00:23:46,080 --> 00:23:47,720
- All you do is lie to me! Go!
- Please calm down.

342
00:23:47,800 --> 00:23:49,160
- Pie!
- Please calm down.

343
00:23:49,240 --> 00:23:50,600
Please don't hurt Pie.

344
00:23:52,120 --> 00:23:54,520
You're the one named Win, aren't you?

345
00:23:54,600 --> 00:23:55,920
I'm Win.

346
00:23:56,720 --> 00:23:57,920
Please calm down first, Mom.

347
00:23:58,000 --> 00:23:59,000
Let me explain.

348
00:23:59,080 --> 00:24:00,440
I won't listen.

349
00:24:00,520 --> 00:24:03,440
And don't call me "Mom."
I'm not your mother.

350
00:24:03,520 --> 00:24:06,640
Who do you think you are,
doing this to my daughter?

351
00:24:06,720 --> 00:24:09,040
Why are you deceiving her? You bastard!

352
00:24:09,120 --> 00:24:10,760
- You scum!
- Mom!

353
00:24:10,840 --> 00:24:12,400
- That's enough! Stop!
- Let go!

354
00:24:12,480 --> 00:24:14,080
- Why are you hurting each other?
- Let go!

355
00:24:14,160 --> 00:24:15,600
Who are you?

356
00:24:15,680 --> 00:24:16,760
I'm the owner here.

357
00:24:18,000 --> 00:24:19,040
Why do you have to hurt each other?

358
00:24:19,120 --> 00:24:21,040
Win is my nephew.

359
00:24:21,120 --> 00:24:22,480
Get out of my daughter's life!

360
00:24:22,560 --> 00:24:23,600
- Get out!
- Mom!

361
00:24:23,680 --> 00:24:25,920
- Please let me explain.
- I won't listen! Let go!

362
00:24:26,000 --> 00:24:27,240
I won't listen to anything!

363
00:24:27,320 --> 00:24:28,840
- Mom!
- Please calm down.

364
00:24:28,920 --> 00:24:30,200
Come home with me now, Pie!

365
00:24:30,280 --> 00:24:31,960
Whoa, she's ridiculously strong!

366
00:24:32,040 --> 00:24:34,640
Win, take her out!

367
00:24:34,720 --> 00:24:36,320
Deal with it yourselves.

368
00:24:37,080 --> 00:24:39,000
Let go of me! Oh my God!

369
00:24:39,080 --> 00:24:40,960
- You bastard! You scum!
- Please calm down!

370
00:24:41,040 --> 00:24:42,080
- Let me go!
- Aunt Saen.

371
00:24:42,160 --> 00:24:44,040
Let go of me!

372
00:24:44,120 --> 00:24:45,480
Put me down right now!

373
00:24:45,560 --> 00:24:48,160
You bastard! You scum!

374
00:24:50,480 --> 00:24:52,280
I have only one daughter.

375
00:24:52,360 --> 00:24:54,200
How could you do this to her?

376
00:24:54,280 --> 00:24:56,160
I truly love Pie.

377
00:24:56,680 --> 00:24:59,200
I never meant to deceive her.
We love each other.

378
00:24:59,280 --> 00:25:02,360
That's not love. Don't make excuses.

379
00:25:03,040 --> 00:25:04,720
That's called infatuation.

380
00:25:04,800 --> 00:25:06,640
You're fooling yourselves
into thinking it's love.

381
00:25:06,720 --> 00:25:07,920
No.

382
00:25:08,000 --> 00:25:09,440
I'm serious about Pie.

383
00:25:09,960 --> 00:25:11,720
You may think it's infatuation,

384
00:25:11,800 --> 00:25:13,640
but for us, it's love.

385
00:25:13,720 --> 00:25:17,240
I'm serious. I'm trying my best
to make her happy.

386
00:25:17,320 --> 00:25:20,880
You think a guy like you
can make her happy?

387
00:25:21,600 --> 00:25:24,120
Look at you.
You can't even take care of yourself.

388
00:25:24,200 --> 00:25:25,680
Can you give me a chance?

389
00:25:25,760 --> 00:25:27,760
- I promise--
- Don't make promises!

390
00:25:27,840 --> 00:25:30,640
Pie's father made promises to me
just like that.

391
00:25:30,720 --> 00:25:32,920
Promises, and couldn't do anything.

392
00:25:33,920 --> 00:25:37,200
If you truly love my daughter,

393
00:25:37,280 --> 00:25:40,480
you should know you're not ready.

394
00:25:40,560 --> 00:25:44,080
You should improve yourself first
before making promises!

395
00:25:47,280 --> 00:25:51,360
Do you know how hard it was to raise her?

396
00:25:51,880 --> 00:25:54,840
I sacrificed everything
so she could have a good life.

397
00:25:56,080 --> 00:25:59,040
If you really love my daughter,

398
00:25:59,560 --> 00:26:01,120
you have to let her go.

399
00:26:01,200 --> 00:26:03,560
Let her meet someone better.
Let her have a good future.

400
00:26:03,640 --> 00:26:05,320
Don't ruin it.

401
00:26:05,400 --> 00:26:08,640
Don't make her endure hardship
with someone like you.

402
00:26:09,240 --> 00:26:11,040
That's not love.

403
00:26:11,120 --> 00:26:12,920
That's selfishness.

404
00:26:15,160 --> 00:26:17,080
Get out.

405
00:26:18,000 --> 00:26:20,560
Don't ever interfere
with my daughter again.

406
00:26:25,160 --> 00:26:29,080
Ma'am, I understand
everything you're saying,

407
00:26:30,640 --> 00:26:32,400
but I really can't leave Pie.

408
00:26:34,440 --> 00:26:36,320
You won't go?

409
00:26:37,040 --> 00:26:37,960
Fine.

410
00:26:38,800 --> 00:26:42,040
If you won't go, I will.

411
00:26:50,040 --> 00:26:52,600
If I have to watch
my daughter's life fall apart

412
00:26:52,680 --> 00:26:55,160
and see her with someone
who has no future, like you,

413
00:26:55,240 --> 00:26:57,320
I'd rather die.

414
00:26:58,440 --> 00:27:00,640
Ma'am, please calm down.

415
00:27:01,480 --> 00:27:03,040
Let's talk this through.

416
00:27:04,400 --> 00:27:07,120
I don't want to fight with my daughter.

417
00:27:07,200 --> 00:27:12,000
But I can't stand
watching her walk into hell,

418
00:27:12,080 --> 00:27:14,080
into a marriage with no future.

419
00:27:14,680 --> 00:27:16,200
If you won't leave,

420
00:27:16,280 --> 00:27:18,400
- I will!
- Ma'am!

421
00:27:20,160 --> 00:27:24,320
Let me go right now! I said let go!

422
00:27:24,400 --> 00:27:25,520
Ma'am.

423
00:27:26,040 --> 00:27:26,920
Ma'am.

424
00:27:29,640 --> 00:27:31,400
Please don't do this.

425
00:27:32,200 --> 00:27:33,920
You won't leave, right?

426
00:27:37,280 --> 00:27:39,240
Ma'am! Okay!

427
00:27:46,600 --> 00:27:47,760
I'll go.

428
00:28:16,400 --> 00:28:17,960
Don't cry.

429
00:29:44,600 --> 00:29:46,000
Let's end it here.

430
00:30:00,120 --> 00:30:01,680
What does that mean?

431
00:30:03,800 --> 00:30:05,440
What did you talk to my mom about?

432
00:30:05,520 --> 00:30:07,920
Why are you saying this?
Did she tell you to say this?

433
00:30:10,360 --> 00:30:13,240
No one told me to. I'm saying this myself.

434
00:30:42,920 --> 00:30:44,000
Pie…

435
00:30:47,640 --> 00:30:49,240
I love you, Pie.

436
00:30:51,000 --> 00:30:53,320
But maybe our relationship
really is moving too fast.

437
00:30:54,720 --> 00:30:56,280
That's why the adults can't accept it.

438
00:30:57,480 --> 00:30:59,680
Then we explain it to them together.

439
00:30:59,760 --> 00:31:02,200
Why are you giving up so easily?

440
00:31:03,920 --> 00:31:05,280
I'm not giving up.

441
00:31:06,600 --> 00:31:08,840
I'm deciding based on reality.

442
00:31:10,200 --> 00:31:12,640
I've received a scholarship
to study in Japan.

443
00:31:13,600 --> 00:31:15,280
We'll be apart for years.

444
00:31:15,360 --> 00:31:18,760
It's not that long.
It's only two years, Win.

445
00:31:19,280 --> 00:31:21,640
And it has nothing to do with our love.

446
00:31:21,720 --> 00:31:23,120
It does, Pie.

447
00:31:23,640 --> 00:31:25,040
It really does.

448
00:31:29,960 --> 00:31:32,480
I want us both to be free.

449
00:31:35,040 --> 00:31:36,440
While I'm away,

450
00:31:38,040 --> 00:31:40,000
if you meet someone better,

451
00:31:41,880 --> 00:31:43,760
you won't miss your chance.

452
00:31:47,120 --> 00:31:47,960
Win.

453
00:31:48,680 --> 00:31:51,760
You know I'm not like that.

454
00:31:53,080 --> 00:31:55,680
Love isn't about choosing
whoever is better.

455
00:31:56,280 --> 00:31:59,440
I love you for who you are.
Do you understand?

456
00:31:59,520 --> 00:32:01,200
Do you?

457
00:32:02,760 --> 00:32:05,240
But love alone isn't enough.

458
00:32:15,840 --> 00:32:17,920
It's just that your love
isn't strong enough.

459
00:32:19,280 --> 00:32:22,760
When problems come,
you let it go so easily.

460
00:32:23,400 --> 00:32:25,840
Didn't you say
we'd fight through this together?

461
00:32:25,920 --> 00:32:28,920
Didn't you say
we'd turn coincidence into destiny?

462
00:32:30,080 --> 00:32:31,960
Why are you doing this?

463
00:32:32,480 --> 00:32:35,000
All those things you said,
they sounded cool,

464
00:32:35,080 --> 00:32:37,400
but they weren't real, were they?

465
00:33:18,120 --> 00:33:19,320
Would you like some water?

466
00:33:25,440 --> 00:33:26,960
I'll just leave it here.

467
00:33:33,320 --> 00:33:35,360
You could at least say no nicely.

468
00:34:08,679 --> 00:34:11,000
I want our love to truly be good.

469
00:34:13,520 --> 00:34:15,480
But right now, I have nothing.

470
00:34:17,800 --> 00:34:19,280
No money.

471
00:34:20,040 --> 00:34:21,320
No job.

472
00:34:23,040 --> 00:34:25,159
And I'm going abroad to study.

473
00:34:26,840 --> 00:34:28,639
I'm not ready to take care of you.

474
00:34:31,120 --> 00:34:32,320
Win.

475
00:34:32,400 --> 00:34:35,520
I never asked you to take care of me.

476
00:34:35,600 --> 00:34:37,960
When you had nothing, I never complained.

477
00:34:38,679 --> 00:34:40,760
Why can't we just build it
together slowly?

478
00:34:41,920 --> 00:34:44,080
Just don't let go of my hand, Win.

479
00:34:44,600 --> 00:34:46,000
Can we?

480
00:34:55,080 --> 00:34:57,080
Can we fight through this together?

481
00:34:58,160 --> 00:35:00,320
Can you not leave me?

482
00:35:00,840 --> 00:35:02,120
Please.

483
00:35:19,760 --> 00:35:21,160
I love you, Pie.

484
00:35:23,040 --> 00:35:24,360
I really do.

485
00:35:28,440 --> 00:35:30,160
But I'm truly not ready.

486
00:35:31,640 --> 00:35:32,760
Win.

487
00:35:33,720 --> 00:35:37,120
Then go make yourself ready.
I'll wait for you.

488
00:35:37,640 --> 00:35:40,320
Okay? Please?

489
00:35:42,880 --> 00:35:44,040
Don't wait.

490
00:35:48,440 --> 00:35:49,760
Don't wait?

491
00:35:53,080 --> 00:35:54,880
So, are we breaking up?

492
00:36:05,280 --> 00:36:07,560
Let's not bind ourselves with a title.

493
00:36:10,640 --> 00:36:12,640
I don't want you to struggle
because of me.

494
00:36:15,320 --> 00:36:17,120
I don't want to be selfish.

495
00:36:24,360 --> 00:36:25,960
We really can't go on.

496
00:36:30,520 --> 00:36:32,560
Are we really breaking up?

497
00:37:01,640 --> 00:37:04,000
Win. Win.

498
00:37:39,640 --> 00:37:40,600
Win.

499
00:37:52,680 --> 00:37:54,040
Win…

500
00:38:15,640 --> 00:38:17,640
Win! Where are you going?

501
00:38:17,720 --> 00:38:19,000
Let's talk first!

502
00:38:20,880 --> 00:38:22,600
This isn't going to end well.

503
00:38:29,080 --> 00:38:31,480
What did he say to you, Pie?

504
00:38:31,560 --> 00:38:33,960
Why are you crying this hard?

505
00:38:34,040 --> 00:38:36,000
What did he do to you?

506
00:38:36,080 --> 00:38:37,960
- Tell me, Pie.
- Mom.

507
00:39:13,960 --> 00:39:15,360
Can you lower it a bit?

508
00:39:15,440 --> 00:39:16,520
Lower what?

509
00:39:16,600 --> 00:39:18,520
The room rent.

510
00:39:18,600 --> 00:39:21,040
Your nephew sleeps with my daughter too.

511
00:39:21,120 --> 00:39:23,160
You expect my daughter to pay alone?

512
00:39:23,240 --> 00:39:25,480
- Let's split it half and half.
- Split it?

513
00:39:25,560 --> 00:39:26,600
Yes.

514
00:39:26,680 --> 00:39:30,080
I saw your nephew's toothbrush, clothes.
His stuff is everywhere.

515
00:39:30,160 --> 00:39:31,480
That means he's using the room too.

516
00:39:31,560 --> 00:39:32,880
Shouldn't he help pay?

517
00:39:32,960 --> 00:39:34,080
How could you think that?

518
00:39:34,160 --> 00:39:35,880
And how could you not?

519
00:39:36,800 --> 00:39:38,840
Honestly, even half is too much,

520
00:39:38,920 --> 00:39:40,880
considering what your nephew
did to my daughter.

521
00:39:42,360 --> 00:39:44,480
You talk like my nephew assaulted her.

522
00:39:44,560 --> 00:39:46,600
They both wanted it.

523
00:39:46,680 --> 00:39:48,360
The only one not right in the head is you.

524
00:39:48,440 --> 00:39:50,760
The kids love each other,
and you can't accept it.

525
00:39:50,840 --> 00:39:52,640
Are you calling me crazy?

526
00:39:53,560 --> 00:39:55,160
- Hey!
- Come on then!

527
00:39:55,760 --> 00:39:57,840
You slap me, I slap back. Fair and square!

528
00:39:57,920 --> 00:39:58,960
Come on! Bring it!

529
00:40:00,560 --> 00:40:03,360
In this life and the next,
I hope we never meet again.

530
00:40:04,560 --> 00:40:08,280
<i>May this merit share with all beings</i>
<i>May they be happy</i>

531
00:40:08,360 --> 00:40:10,920
<i>May all beings be happy</i>

532
00:40:11,000 --> 00:40:13,920
<i>May all beings be blessed with happiness</i>

533
00:40:14,000 --> 00:40:15,400
<i>Sathu</i>

534
00:40:16,880 --> 00:40:18,720
I've dedicated the merit. Still here?

535
00:40:19,280 --> 00:40:21,480
Or do you want me to pour
the water right on you?

536
00:40:21,560 --> 00:40:23,080
- Hey!
- I can do that.

537
00:40:23,160 --> 00:40:24,560
You crazy, rude woman!

538
00:40:24,640 --> 00:40:27,840
Actually, you owe me 50 baht in change.

539
00:40:27,920 --> 00:40:30,000
But forget it. I'll consider it charity.

540
00:40:32,000 --> 00:40:33,560
What did I do to deserve this?

541
00:40:36,720 --> 00:40:40,160
Pie, come on. Let's go home.

542
00:40:40,240 --> 00:40:42,480
Ma'am, should I put the bags
in the car now?

543
00:40:42,560 --> 00:40:43,760
- Yes, please.
- Alright.

544
00:40:43,840 --> 00:40:44,960
- Yes, ma'am.
- Thank you.

545
00:40:45,040 --> 00:40:46,000
Be careful with them. Hey!

546
00:40:46,080 --> 00:40:49,520
- Careful! That bag is expensive.
- Sorry, sorry.

547
00:40:49,600 --> 00:40:52,880
- This one too. Lift it gently.
- Yes, ma'am.

548
00:41:23,520 --> 00:41:26,520
<i>It's my promise that one day,</i>

549
00:41:27,040 --> 00:41:30,920
<i>I'll help you live freely,</i>
<i>the way you want to.</i>

550
00:41:31,000 --> 00:41:32,520
<i>Just like this bird.</i>

551
00:42:52,320 --> 00:42:56,680
- <i>I love you the most, Pie!</i>
- <i>I love you the most, Win!</i>

552
00:43:12,640 --> 00:43:15,520
Cheers.

553
00:43:16,840 --> 00:43:18,280
Cheers.

554
00:43:22,120 --> 00:43:24,000
Hey, Sil.

555
00:43:24,600 --> 00:43:27,040
The land in Ratchaburi
you asked me to find,

556
00:43:27,120 --> 00:43:28,360
I found a few good plots.

557
00:43:28,440 --> 00:43:30,600
Prices haven't gone up much yet.
Take a look.

558
00:43:30,680 --> 00:43:33,920
- Oh, nice. Really nice.
- Of course.

559
00:43:34,000 --> 00:43:35,680
But pictures alone aren't enough.

560
00:43:35,760 --> 00:43:39,080
We have to go see the land in person
and check the soil condition too.

561
00:43:39,600 --> 00:43:40,440
Alright?

562
00:43:41,040 --> 00:43:43,080
Let me ask you honestly. Are you serious?

563
00:43:44,520 --> 00:43:45,360
Of course.

564
00:43:45,440 --> 00:43:47,400
Farmer's blood runs in my veins.

565
00:43:47,480 --> 00:43:49,600
I want to farm.

566
00:43:49,680 --> 00:43:51,480
Will your wife allow it?

567
00:43:52,840 --> 00:43:55,520
If she won't, she doesn't have to come.

568
00:43:55,600 --> 00:43:56,760
Even better.

569
00:43:56,840 --> 00:43:58,880
I want to farm with the villagers.

570
00:43:58,960 --> 00:44:00,320
To live peacefully.

571
00:44:00,400 --> 00:44:02,560
- It's my life!
- Wait.

572
00:44:02,640 --> 00:44:04,480
You're talking
like your home isn't peaceful.

573
00:44:05,080 --> 00:44:06,000
Peaceful.

574
00:44:06,080 --> 00:44:07,520
Very peaceful.

575
00:44:07,600 --> 00:44:10,080
Like a battlefield.

576
00:44:10,160 --> 00:44:13,520
One wrong step and boom!
Explosions everywhere.

577
00:44:13,600 --> 00:44:16,720
Oh, you're exaggerating.

578
00:44:16,800 --> 00:44:18,160
How so?

579
00:44:18,240 --> 00:44:20,840
- Ask Pun.
- Yes, ask me.

580
00:44:20,920 --> 00:44:24,320
I'm neutral. I don't get involved in wars.

581
00:44:24,920 --> 00:44:26,040
- Oh?
- I'll go find Rok.

582
00:44:26,120 --> 00:44:27,520
- Hold on.
- Pun!

583
00:44:27,600 --> 00:44:29,840
- Come back and tell me.
- Pun!

584
00:44:29,920 --> 00:44:31,480
- That peace ambassador!
- Don't! Pun.

585
00:44:41,440 --> 00:44:42,480
Rok!

586
00:44:43,240 --> 00:44:44,280
Rok.

587
00:44:47,080 --> 00:44:48,600
What's wrong? Why are you crying?

588
00:44:49,480 --> 00:44:50,800
Tell me. Who hurt you?

589
00:44:53,920 --> 00:44:56,080
Pun, don't tell Mom.

590
00:44:58,280 --> 00:45:00,520
Okay, I won't.

591
00:45:01,120 --> 00:45:03,520
But tell me what happened.

592
00:45:05,920 --> 00:45:08,360
I talked to Pie's mom on the phone.

593
00:45:09,160 --> 00:45:13,480
She scolded me so badly,
I didn't even have time to apologize.

594
00:45:18,400 --> 00:45:20,040
Why did she scold you?

595
00:45:22,560 --> 00:45:24,040
Tell me, Rok.

596
00:45:24,560 --> 00:45:25,720
Alright.

597
00:45:26,760 --> 00:45:28,200
I promise

598
00:45:28,800 --> 00:45:30,400
I won't scold you for this.

599
00:45:32,560 --> 00:45:34,240
<i>Her mother is very controlling.</i>

600
00:45:34,840 --> 00:45:36,720
She wants to match Pun
with her friend's niece.

601
00:45:36,800 --> 00:45:38,560
What year does she think this is?

602
00:45:38,640 --> 00:45:39,840
The 1950s?

603
00:45:39,920 --> 00:45:42,000
Still arranging marriages.

604
00:45:42,080 --> 00:45:43,320
So old-fashioned!

605
00:45:43,400 --> 00:45:45,520
- Exactly. Very outdated.
- Yeah.

606
00:45:45,600 --> 00:45:47,760
You can't force someone's heart.

607
00:45:47,840 --> 00:45:49,800
Doesn't Pun already like someone?

608
00:45:49,880 --> 00:45:51,160
- Really?
- What?

609
00:45:51,240 --> 00:45:53,400
- You don't know?
- And you do?

610
00:45:54,000 --> 00:45:56,120
No! You're his father and you don't know.

611
00:45:56,200 --> 00:45:58,680
- How would I?
- Wait, don't drink yet.

612
00:45:59,720 --> 00:46:00,800
You're acting suspicious.

613
00:46:00,880 --> 00:46:03,640
You just said he likes someone.

614
00:46:03,720 --> 00:46:06,040
I was guessing. Can't I guess?

615
00:46:06,120 --> 00:46:09,720
He's grown up already.
Of course he might like someone.

616
00:46:12,120 --> 00:46:14,920
But if he does like someone, I pity him.

617
00:46:15,800 --> 00:46:17,640
- Why?
- Well.

618
00:46:17,720 --> 00:46:21,680
If his mother doesn't like the girl,
it's chaos at home.

619
00:46:21,760 --> 00:46:23,160
Trust me.

620
00:46:33,480 --> 00:46:35,920
Pie asked me to help her.

621
00:46:36,000 --> 00:46:38,360
I felt sorry for her, so I helped.

622
00:46:39,520 --> 00:46:41,840
Pun, Pie's pitiful.

623
00:46:41,920 --> 00:46:44,080
Her mom controls her like a prisoner.

624
00:46:44,160 --> 00:46:45,800
She didn't want to lie.

625
00:46:45,880 --> 00:46:47,440
But if she didn't,

626
00:46:47,520 --> 00:46:49,720
her mom wouldn't let her
finish her graduation project.

627
00:46:52,040 --> 00:46:53,240
I understand.

628
00:46:54,400 --> 00:46:57,080
Anyone would be angry in this situation.

629
00:47:00,520 --> 00:47:02,320
But I understand Pie too.

630
00:47:02,400 --> 00:47:04,160
I understand both sides.

631
00:47:07,080 --> 00:47:08,280
Rok.

632
00:47:08,920 --> 00:47:11,400
You should apologize
to Pie's mom properly.

633
00:47:13,440 --> 00:47:14,760
No way!

634
00:47:14,840 --> 00:47:17,920
If I go, she'll just yell at me again.
Forget it!

635
00:47:18,000 --> 00:47:19,960
Even if she does, you have to accept it.

636
00:47:20,040 --> 00:47:21,640
Because you were wrong.

637
00:47:23,000 --> 00:47:24,720
And remember this.

638
00:47:24,800 --> 00:47:27,280
Don't help your friends lie again.

639
00:47:27,800 --> 00:47:28,680
Got it?

640
00:47:33,080 --> 00:47:33,960
How about this?

641
00:47:35,120 --> 00:47:36,360
I'll go with you.

642
00:47:36,960 --> 00:47:39,960
Maybe I can help,
so it's not as bad as we think.

643
00:47:43,080 --> 00:47:44,320
How will you help?

644
00:48:02,840 --> 00:48:04,560
I'm sorry, Auntie.

645
00:48:06,760 --> 00:48:08,160
Mom, please don't be mad at Rok.

646
00:48:08,800 --> 00:48:10,600
She didn't do anything wrong.

647
00:48:10,680 --> 00:48:13,040
I forced her to help me.

648
00:48:13,680 --> 00:48:16,760
If you're mad, be mad at me, not her.

649
00:48:17,280 --> 00:48:18,800
I'm sorry, Mom.

650
00:48:19,520 --> 00:48:20,360
Pie.

651
00:48:22,800 --> 00:48:24,720
The only mistake she made was trusting me.

652
00:48:25,240 --> 00:48:26,520
Everything else isn't her fault.

653
00:48:27,120 --> 00:48:28,040
I'm sorry.

654
00:48:28,120 --> 00:48:30,960
You two were in it together.

655
00:48:31,040 --> 00:48:33,640
If I hadn't caught you,
would you even apologize?

656
00:48:34,240 --> 00:48:37,320
You'd just keep teaming up
and let me stay fooled forever.

657
00:48:38,560 --> 00:48:39,440
Excuse me.

658
00:48:40,160 --> 00:48:43,560
Well… Rok is still young.

659
00:48:43,640 --> 00:48:46,000
She lied because she cares
about her friend.

660
00:48:46,800 --> 00:48:48,080
But she regrets it now.

661
00:48:48,160 --> 00:48:49,680
Please forgive her.

662
00:48:49,760 --> 00:48:52,400
Who are you? Why are you interfering?

663
00:48:54,240 --> 00:48:55,440
Mom.

664
00:48:55,520 --> 00:48:57,360
Rok already introduced him earlier.

665
00:48:57,440 --> 00:49:00,480
I was too busy being angry.
I wasn't paying attention.

666
00:49:01,840 --> 00:49:05,280
That's okay. I'll introduce myself again.

667
00:49:05,880 --> 00:49:08,600
My name is Pun. I'm Rok's cousin.

668
00:49:08,680 --> 00:49:09,960
Do you have a business card?

669
00:49:19,760 --> 00:49:20,800
KHUN PUN
PARIT PITTHAKORN, CEO

670
00:49:20,880 --> 00:49:22,440
Khun Pun Co., Ltd?

671
00:49:22,520 --> 00:49:23,880
It's my own company.

672
00:49:25,120 --> 00:49:27,000
Please trust Rok this once.

673
00:49:28,600 --> 00:49:33,240
She promised me this won't happen again.

674
00:49:33,320 --> 00:49:34,840
Please forgive her.

675
00:49:38,360 --> 00:49:40,120
For your brother's sake,

676
00:49:40,720 --> 00:49:42,360
I'll forgive both of you.

677
00:49:42,960 --> 00:49:45,120
But you two know, right?

678
00:49:45,200 --> 00:49:47,920
I scold you because I care.

679
00:49:48,520 --> 00:49:49,960
From now on,

680
00:49:50,760 --> 00:49:52,760
don't lie to me again.

681
00:49:52,840 --> 00:49:55,880
Don't do things behind my back.

682
00:49:55,960 --> 00:50:00,040
If something bad happens
or you meet bad people,

683
00:50:00,560 --> 00:50:02,120
the ones who will get hurt

684
00:50:02,680 --> 00:50:03,880
are you.

685
00:50:16,080 --> 00:50:19,560
Thank you so much, Pun,
for helping calm my mom down.

686
00:50:21,480 --> 00:50:24,680
Rok, thank you too.

687
00:50:25,280 --> 00:50:27,760
I'm sorry you got scolded because of me.

688
00:50:28,960 --> 00:50:30,640
I'm really sorry.

689
00:50:32,640 --> 00:50:34,040
Hey.

690
00:50:34,120 --> 00:50:36,680
It's nothing. Don't be so dramatic.

691
00:50:36,760 --> 00:50:38,080
You'll make me cry again.

692
00:50:38,160 --> 00:50:40,200
But I'm curious though.

693
00:50:40,280 --> 00:50:42,080
Why did your mom get that furious?

694
00:50:43,080 --> 00:50:44,560
Did something happen there?

695
00:50:48,000 --> 00:50:50,120
She explodes over nothing anyway.

696
00:50:50,840 --> 00:50:52,480
Since I lied, she got even angrier.

697
00:50:53,440 --> 00:50:55,680
Pun, I'm sorry too.

698
00:50:55,760 --> 00:50:58,200
You had to waste your time helping us.

699
00:50:58,880 --> 00:51:01,120
Don't bow to me and don't apologize.

700
00:51:03,200 --> 00:51:04,400
Just treat me to a meal.

701
00:51:08,120 --> 00:51:11,560
Okay. Rok and I will treat you.

702
00:51:14,440 --> 00:51:15,320
Pie.

703
00:51:15,960 --> 00:51:17,640
Why am I included?

704
00:51:18,520 --> 00:51:20,520
Pun helped both of us.

705
00:51:20,600 --> 00:51:22,240
We should repay him together.

706
00:51:22,320 --> 00:51:23,600
How can I treat him alone?

707
00:51:24,200 --> 00:51:25,480
Right, Pun?

708
00:51:27,640 --> 00:51:29,120
After insisting like that,

709
00:51:29,640 --> 00:51:31,200
I guess it has to be yes.

710
00:51:31,960 --> 00:51:33,360
Huh? Hey.

711
00:51:34,080 --> 00:51:36,520
My brother gave in so easily. What's this?

712
00:51:37,960 --> 00:51:40,680
Fine! I'll treat him too.

713
00:51:42,680 --> 00:51:44,520
I'm heading off. See you later.

714
00:51:44,600 --> 00:51:46,240
- Bye.
- Bye.

715
00:51:46,320 --> 00:51:47,440
Come here.

716
00:51:47,520 --> 00:51:48,800
- Get in.
- Yeah, get in the car.

717
00:51:48,880 --> 00:51:50,440
- Get in the car.
- You get in the car.

718
00:51:50,960 --> 00:51:52,200
- Bye.
- See you.

719
00:51:56,680 --> 00:51:57,680
Pie.

720
00:51:57,760 --> 00:52:01,160
Rok's brother is from an old
and well-established family.

721
00:52:01,240 --> 00:52:03,280
The Pitthakorn family.

722
00:52:03,360 --> 00:52:05,880
His mother used to work at a university,

723
00:52:05,960 --> 00:52:07,920
but it was more for social connections.

724
00:52:08,000 --> 00:52:10,000
She quit after a few years.

725
00:52:10,080 --> 00:52:11,840
Their family is wealthy enough

726
00:52:11,920 --> 00:52:15,080
that she can live comfortably
without working.

727
00:52:15,160 --> 00:52:18,520
They're very rich and well-established.

728
00:52:18,600 --> 00:52:20,720
But his father is still working.

729
00:52:20,800 --> 00:52:22,840
He's a consultant
for several organizations.

730
00:52:22,920 --> 00:52:25,280
Mom, I just dropped Pun off.

731
00:52:25,360 --> 00:52:26,680
How do you know all that?

732
00:52:27,720 --> 00:52:33,560
Well, he looked promising,
so I did a little research, that's all.

733
00:52:34,160 --> 00:52:35,240
I see.

734
00:52:35,320 --> 00:52:36,160
Hold on, Pie.

735
00:52:37,600 --> 00:52:42,480
Why did Rok's brother
step in to help you two?

736
00:52:43,000 --> 00:52:44,080
Is he interested in you?

737
00:52:44,160 --> 00:52:47,040
Mom, no!

738
00:52:48,960 --> 00:52:52,240
Rok was stressed, so he just came to help.

739
00:52:53,200 --> 00:52:54,360
What a pity.

740
00:52:54,440 --> 00:52:58,120
I never knew
Rok had such wealthy relatives.

741
00:52:58,200 --> 00:53:01,240
Just look at the car he drives,
the watch he wears.

742
00:53:01,320 --> 00:53:03,960
Very good taste.

743
00:53:04,880 --> 00:53:06,080
Yes.

744
00:53:07,040 --> 00:53:08,640
Wait, Pie.

745
00:53:10,640 --> 00:53:13,680
Did you tell Rok about that man?

746
00:53:14,560 --> 00:53:15,640
No, I didn't.

747
00:53:17,240 --> 00:53:18,080
Good.

748
00:53:18,680 --> 00:53:21,800
What happened before was a mistake.

749
00:53:22,400 --> 00:53:24,200
You made a mistake,
and now you start over.

750
00:53:24,720 --> 00:53:28,960
But this matter,
you must not let anyone know.

751
00:53:29,720 --> 00:53:31,040
Not even Rok.

752
00:53:31,120 --> 00:53:33,280
No matter how close you are,

753
00:53:33,360 --> 00:53:35,120
don't say a word.

754
00:53:35,720 --> 00:53:37,440
Can you promise me?

755
00:53:39,160 --> 00:53:40,000
‪Yes.

756
00:53:41,480 --> 00:53:43,240
I won't tell anyone.

757
00:53:46,200 --> 00:53:48,960
People make mistakes.

758
00:53:49,560 --> 00:53:51,120
Just treat it as a lesson.

759
00:53:51,200 --> 00:53:54,640
Life goes on.

760
00:53:55,360 --> 00:53:56,720
You understand, right?

761
00:54:01,040 --> 00:54:02,760
I understand, Mom.

762
00:54:06,040 --> 00:54:07,640
Good girl.

763
00:54:15,280 --> 00:54:17,200
Thanks. Hey.

764
00:54:17,280 --> 00:54:19,240
Now that you've graduated, what's next?

765
00:54:19,320 --> 00:54:23,000
Still planning to study abroad,
like we discussed?

766
00:54:23,080 --> 00:54:24,400
I don't want to study anymore.

767
00:54:24,480 --> 00:54:27,240
If you don't want to study,
what do you want to do?

768
00:54:27,320 --> 00:54:28,480
I want a boyfriend.

769
00:54:33,000 --> 00:54:34,040
Are you serious?

770
00:54:34,120 --> 00:54:36,320
I am. I like Pun.

771
00:54:36,400 --> 00:54:37,960
- I know.
- I want him.

772
00:54:38,040 --> 00:54:39,520
Whoa, that's a bit much.

773
00:54:39,600 --> 00:54:40,840
I'm serious.

774
00:54:40,920 --> 00:54:43,400
My life has to include Pun.

775
00:54:43,480 --> 00:54:46,520
Please help me cheer him on.

776
00:54:46,600 --> 00:54:50,640
Hey, you can't force something like that.

777
00:54:50,720 --> 00:54:52,400
It's destiny, right?

778
00:54:52,480 --> 00:54:54,680
More like karma.

779
00:54:55,560 --> 00:54:56,920
Come on, Uncle.

780
00:54:58,520 --> 00:55:01,400
I'm not going to sit around
waiting for karma to work.

781
00:55:01,480 --> 00:55:02,520
What are you going to do?

782
00:55:02,600 --> 00:55:04,800
- I'm going to make the first move.
- Oh dear.

783
00:55:04,880 --> 00:55:07,720
If you won't support me,
at least give me some advice.

784
00:55:07,800 --> 00:55:09,880
If I want to win Pun's heart,
what should I do?

785
00:55:09,960 --> 00:55:13,920
Please?

786
00:55:17,280 --> 00:55:19,520
Uncle asked me to bring
these scones for you.

787
00:55:31,640 --> 00:55:34,200
It's rare to meet someone
who knows how to eat a scone.

788
00:55:35,240 --> 00:55:38,560
It's hot inside.
You'll burn your mouth otherwise.

789
00:55:38,640 --> 00:55:40,320
Uncle taught me.

790
00:55:40,400 --> 00:55:42,200
Let's meet again sometime.

791
00:55:42,280 --> 00:55:45,680
Then you can meet Pun too.
I'd like you two to get acquainted.

792
00:55:45,760 --> 00:55:48,640
You might be able to help
each other in the future.

793
00:55:49,360 --> 00:55:51,120
Of course, Auntie. Thank you very much.

794
00:55:51,200 --> 00:55:52,080
You're welcome.

795
00:55:56,840 --> 00:56:02,600
FOR SALE

796
00:56:24,960 --> 00:56:27,840
Is this the home of Mr. San
and Mrs. Ketsinee Kritanon?

797
00:56:27,920 --> 00:56:31,320
We received a report that your parents

798
00:56:31,400 --> 00:56:32,800
were in an accident on the highway.

799
00:56:33,480 --> 00:56:36,760
They both passed away. I'm very sorry.

800
00:56:40,120 --> 00:56:41,320
Koh!

801
00:56:46,640 --> 00:56:47,480
Pun.

802
00:56:51,560 --> 00:56:52,640
How've you been?

803
00:56:52,720 --> 00:56:54,800
When did you get back?

804
00:56:54,880 --> 00:56:56,680
How are things?

805
00:56:57,280 --> 00:56:59,200
You came to Bangkok
and didn't even tell me.

806
00:56:59,840 --> 00:57:02,440
I've been busy with a lot of things.
I forgot to tell you.

807
00:57:04,120 --> 00:57:07,400
Didn't you say you were doing better?

808
00:57:07,480 --> 00:57:09,400
Why so gloomy?

809
00:57:10,280 --> 00:57:13,320
Or did seeing your old house again
bring back memories?

810
00:57:15,720 --> 00:57:17,080
Something like that.

811
00:57:18,520 --> 00:57:21,240
Hey, come on.

812
00:57:21,320 --> 00:57:23,600
Being sad won't change anything.

813
00:57:24,200 --> 00:57:26,160
You worked so hard
to recover all this time.

814
00:57:26,920 --> 00:57:28,520
Come on. Let's cheer up.

815
00:57:28,600 --> 00:57:31,760
Come inside.
My dad's been asking about you.

816
00:57:32,440 --> 00:57:33,440
Hey, what about my bag?

817
00:57:33,520 --> 00:57:34,640
Don't worry. I'll get someone.

818
00:57:34,720 --> 00:57:35,840
Alright.

819
00:57:35,920 --> 00:57:38,080
FOR AUNT SAEN

820
00:57:38,720 --> 00:57:40,440
DONATION ITEMS

821
00:57:43,400 --> 00:57:45,840
Hey. You done sorting things out?

822
00:57:45,920 --> 00:57:47,000
Almost.

823
00:57:47,080 --> 00:57:50,320
Could you donate these boxes for me?

824
00:57:50,400 --> 00:57:52,960
I'll send the rest to Aunt Saen.

825
00:57:53,040 --> 00:57:55,360
Sure. I'll have someone take care of it.

826
00:58:02,800 --> 00:58:03,840
What's this?

827
00:58:07,760 --> 00:58:08,920
I exchanged some money.

828
00:58:09,440 --> 00:58:12,400
Even with a scholarship,
you'll still need money there.

829
00:58:14,000 --> 00:58:16,120
No, Pun. I really can't accept this.

830
00:58:16,200 --> 00:58:17,520
Hey, it's fine.

831
00:58:17,600 --> 00:58:19,280
I want you to have it.

832
00:58:19,360 --> 00:58:21,200
I don't know
how to repay you for everything.

833
00:58:21,280 --> 00:58:22,200
Forget it.

834
00:58:22,880 --> 00:58:25,120
When you get a job after you come back,

835
00:58:25,640 --> 00:58:27,000
you can pay me then.

836
00:58:28,080 --> 00:58:29,880
If I'm ever in trouble, you can help me.

837
00:58:30,480 --> 00:58:33,280
Right now, you need help,
so let me help you.

838
00:58:34,720 --> 00:58:36,320
Okay? Deal?

839
00:58:39,760 --> 00:58:40,840
Alright.

840
00:58:42,280 --> 00:58:43,480
Thank you so much.

841
00:58:44,000 --> 00:58:47,560
Hey, don't mention it. I'm your brother.

842
00:58:51,960 --> 00:58:54,080
<i>Is Pun interested in you, Pie?</i>

843
00:58:54,160 --> 00:58:55,920
This one gets my approval.

844
00:58:56,000 --> 00:58:57,520
That's a bit fast.

845
00:58:57,600 --> 00:58:58,760
Then,

846
00:58:59,560 --> 00:59:00,640
I must be someone special.

847
00:59:00,720 --> 00:59:03,160
You could say that.

848
00:59:03,240 --> 00:59:06,160
It's like meeting the right person…

849
00:59:06,800 --> 00:59:08,040
…at the wrong time.

850
00:59:08,120 --> 00:59:11,160
If you meet the wrong person
at the right time,

851
00:59:11,240 --> 00:59:12,480
it's still wrong.

852
00:59:12,560 --> 00:59:13,680
Pun, how do you feel about Pie?

853
00:59:13,760 --> 00:59:15,120
I'd like her to be my girlfriend.

854
00:59:16,160 --> 00:59:17,160
I like Pun.

855
00:59:17,240 --> 00:59:19,640
If you want to compete with me,
bring it on.

856
00:59:21,240 --> 00:59:23,120
Even if the whole world says you're good,

857
00:59:25,080 --> 00:59:26,880
<i>I won't back down.</i>

858
00:59:51,960 --> 00:59:54,640
Subtitle translation by:
Chomchanach Yanaharn
